<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1371,1707]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,325,1410,1436]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The species (
<figureCitation box="[486,556,1410,1436]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1843,1867]" captionTargetBox="[151,1410,212,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-69@5.[151,1436,194,1819]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Stenoloba spp., adults. 1. S. yunley, male, holotype; 2. S. yunley, male, paratype; 3. S. viridibasis, male, holotype; 4. S. pulla, male; 5. S. oculatoides, male, holotype; 6. S. benedeki, male; 7. S. viridinivea, male, holotype; 8. S. viridinivea, male, paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5306325" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5306325/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) is characterized by pale olive-green forewing coloration and wing pattern with distinct basal line and dentate, somewhat diffused antemedial line; subterminal line diffused. In male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[268,352,1488,1514]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–29" captionStartId="8.[151,274,1843,1867]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,204,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-75@8.[151,1436,194,1819]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 24–29. Stenoloba spp., male genitalia. 24. S. viridinivea, paratype, genit. prep. HHL-1338-1; 25. S. brunneola, genit. prep. HHL-1220-1; 26. S. viridimicta genit. prep. HHL-1330-1; 27. S. lichenosella, genit. prep. HHL- 1237-1; 28. S. basiviridis, genit. prep. HHL-1247-1; 29. S. benedeki, genit. prep. ZFMK 2021 VK." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5306333" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5306333/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
) uncus developed, flat; valva relatively narrow, with sclerotized bar of clasper, armed on the apex with few short spines. Female genitalia described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ronkay, L." box="[882,1072,1526,1552]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="219 - 229" refId="ref11636" refString="Ronkay, L. 2001. New Stenoloba Staudinger, 1892 species from Taiwan and Vietnam (Lepidoptera: Noctuidae, Bryophilinae). Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationals Hungarici, 93, 219 - 229." type="journal article" year="2001">Ronkay (2001)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ronkay" authorityYear="2001" box="[1086,1227,1527,1552]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Stenoloba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="benedeki">
<emphasis box="[1086,1227,1527,1552]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">S. benedeki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with its allies 
<taxonomicName authority="Kononenko &amp; Ronkay, 2000" authorityName="Kononenko &amp; Ronkay" authorityYear="2000" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Chytonis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olivacea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">S. olivacea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kononenko, V. S. &amp; Ronkay L." box="[259,600,1565,1591]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="137 - 174" refId="ref11520" refString="Kononenko, V. S. &amp; Ronkay L. (2000) A revision of the genus Stenoloba Staudinger, 1892 (Lepidoptera, Noctuidae, Bryophilinae) with description of 25 new species and 3 new subspecies from East Asia (I). Insecta Koreana, 17 (3), 137 - 174." type="journal article" year="2000">Kononenko &amp; Ronkay, 2000</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kononenko &amp; Ronkay, 2000" authorityName="Kononenko &amp; Ronkay" authorityYear="2000" box="[658,1085,1565,1591]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Stenoloba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="futii">
<emphasis box="[658,736,1565,1590]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">S. futii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kononenko, V. S. &amp; Ronkay L." box="[744,1085,1565,1591]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="137 - 174" refId="ref11520" refString="Kononenko, V. S. &amp; Ronkay L. (2000) A revision of the genus Stenoloba Staudinger, 1892 (Lepidoptera, Noctuidae, Bryophilinae) with description of 25 new species and 3 new subspecies from East Asia (I). Insecta Koreana, 17 (3), 137 - 174." type="journal article" year="2000">Kononenko &amp; Ronkay, 2000</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
form a group of species. The last two have not yet been found in 
<collectingCountry box="[575,649,1604,1630]" name="China" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">China</collectingCountry>
. Our record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ronkay" authorityYear="2001" box="[829,964,1604,1629]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Stenoloba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="benedeki">
<emphasis box="[829,964,1604,1629]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">S. benedeki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in an old collection from Prov. 
<collectingRegion box="[1341,1436,1604,1630]" country="China" name="Shaanxi" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Shaanxi</collectingRegion>
significantly extends the distribution of the species northwards.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
